The master bedroom in our home in Arizona is one of my fav rooms in the house!!!!! Definitely wasn’t effortless ! 😂😂😂

Design 911 help: @simplesoutherncharm 

@boujeeinthedesert will be ready to rent by Christmas!!!!

Ahhhhhhhhhhhh I am soooooo excited about the faux beams that we had put in at @boujeeinthedesert!!!! 

The 12 foot ceilings are fabulous but almost made the space feel a little cold. So I knew I wanted some interest and warmth on the ceiling as well as to help bring the eye back down. 

I reached out to @thefantasyfabricators to make the faux beams because the faux ones are so much lighter and less expensive than the real wood ones. 

And it was awesome to hire someone who is basically faux finishing these to look real….. exactly what we used to do on walls with my faux painting company in Kansas City!!!

Watching the install was fascinating! They still have the seams to caulk and paint but I couldn’t wait any longer to post! 😂

And we loved them so much that I had them install faux beams in the master bedroom and hallway also! Those pics are coming!!!

🎉🎉🎉
💃💃💃
❤️❤️❤️

I happen to think this is one sexy looking faucet! 😂😂😂

This is just a testament to the fact that Facebook ads still work because I literally saw this several times on an ad and had to have it. 

Made by @kraususa.

I am smitten. ❤️

I’m obsessed with the focal wood wall that we had @pricklypeachinteriors build for us at @boujeeinthedesert. 

They were able to lay the pattern in a day and our contractors had it primed and sprayed in SW Iron Ore the next day. 

What a big impact it made! May need to do one in our KC house now too!!! 😂😂 If you are in the Phoenix area….. contact @pricklypeachinteriors!!!!!

Have you done a wood wall in your house? *wood* you?? 😂😂

Ok help a sister out….

The first picture is the hallway in  @boujeeinthedesert right now. 

The second picture is of how it used to look, which was so sad. Lol. 

The last picture is an inspiration photo I screenshot ages ago. No idea where it’s from. But I love the BLACK ceiling with the beams. 

Comment below. Should I paint the ceiling in between the beams black or no?

Truth: I totally copied this stair carpet idea from my friend @tallchickinheels. 

Secret: It’s 5 separate runner rugs from @wellwovenrugs used one after another to look like carpet. I LOVE IT!!

(And it’s my favorite next to the black wood wall . See previous reel.)
null

I love this bedroom at @boujeeinthedesert. It has its own en suite bathroom, a black ceiling and floating nightstands (since we kept striking out on the size of every night stand we bought. Lol.) 

Truth: the bench at the end of the bed was one of the very first things I bought for this house, and I bought it off of Facebook marketplace.

Curious if you buy furniture from Facebook marketplace also?

If you’ve followed me since we remodeled @boujeeonthebeach you’ll remember I worked with @battlecreekhardware for all our kitchen and bath hardware in that house. 

When it came time to select hardware for the cabinets at our new AirBNB @boujeeinthedesert ….. I went right back to @battlecreekhardware. They are so kind and so easy to work with without breaking the bank! 

I knew for hardware I wanted big, chunky and bold while also staying timeless and classy. 

I’m obsessed with what they helped me select! 

The pulls are called “Raleigh cup pulls” in honey bronze color. The long bar pulls are also Raleigh in honey bronze and actually come with an optional back plate.

If you’re in the market for new pulls or handles, Battle Creek Hardware is offering all of my followers a 15% off coupon if you use the code “allwood” at checkout. 

No compensation in that for me. Just a really great company to work with and I wanted to pass on that coupon to you!!!!

If you are toying with the idea of GOLD cabinet hardware, you totally should! A good paint job and gold hardware can elevate the look of any cabinet!!!

😘😘😩

Truth: the master bathroom at @boujeeinthedesert was one of my 2 least favorite rooms in the new house. 😩😩

It was a super spacious area. But it was super sterile and felt dark. 

There was no wow factor and I really need that! 😂😂

So we literally gutted the entire thing. We took out the obnoxious built-in tub and replaced it with a standalone.

At the suggestion of  @simplesoutherncharm we built a pony wall in between the shower and the tub which I love so so much!! 

The wallpaper is the same as what is in the master bedroom and it is from  @sarzastore. They were soooooo amazing to work with. 

I would have loved to have taken out the block window but it was going to take several more weeks to complete the project and be so expensive as that window faces the entryway of the house. We were going to have to re-stucco the front side of the house if we replaced that window. 🙈🙈🙈

So, instead I surrounded it with really pretty tile. You might need to zoom in to see it. 

And now one of my least favorite rooms in the house is one of my most favorites!!!!

Look at that before/after!!!

📸: @arizona_real_estate_photos

I have them in our home in KC, in @boujeeonthebeach and 2 of them in @boujeeinthedesert !! 🙈🙈

OK we have never had our own fruit tree of any kind. But at @boujeeinthedesert we have a lemon tree and it is so much fun!!!!

Ari was so excited to make lemon water. But then she also hated it! Lol. 

I loved it!!!! I am convinced that the lemons taste different and so much better when they’re out of your backyard! Lol.

Do you have any fruit trees? Tell me what kind !!

We didn’t gut the kitchen, but close enough. 

The floors have new tile.

The countertops were swapped out for quartz. 

A few of the bulky upper cabinets were taken out and replaced with glass and gold shelving. 

The cabinets were all painted Sherwin-Williams Privileged Green. Notice I had them take the paint up onto the soffit so that the cabinets appeared to be taller.

Cabinet handles were all replaced by @battlecreekhardware . 

Lights are all listed in my Amazon store. Google “Jennifer Allwood Amazon store” and look for my list called “Arizona house”. 

I am so thrilled with how it turned out! What other questions can I answer for you???

Our house in Arizona, @boujeeinthedesert, got 4 more bookings this weekend! 😳😳😳

I am a little stunned and super excited!!!

But……. 

Here is a part of short term rentals that nobody really talks about. 

On Friday morning we got up to have coffee in the living room and Jason saw a huge hole in our tile floor. 😳😳😩😩

Easton‘s girlfriend Bella figured out that it could’ve been the table that sits next to the sofa that fell. And since the bottom of the table is chipped that would make sense.

But here is the conundrum that no one will probably tell you.

Our last guest has not left us a review yet. And there were a few other people inside of the house after our guest doing some work. So we don’t really know how the hole got there? 

So the concern is ….if our management company reaches out to the guest they will probably say they didn’t do it. 

But we could still put in a claim thru VRBO against them for the $450 that it cost to have it fixed. 

But then we run the risk of an awful review. And in the very beginning of a short term rental ….reviews mean everything.

Sharing this with you because many of you are interested in getting started in your first short term rental. And we are learning a lot with our first 2. 

I do have a free 4 part podcast series that is in my link in bio if you’d like to download it and learn all of our advice about your first VRBO and AirBNB! 

Hope it’s helpful!!

Also.. “if you break something, say something!” Lol

We weren’t setting out to own short term rentals. 

We just wanted a 2nd home in Florida. ☀️ 

But then when @boujeeonthebeach was sitting empty for weeks /a few months at a time and people began asking about a rental link ….we started to ponder. 

Now we have @boujeeonthebeach in Florida and @boujeeinthedesert in Arizona and boy have we learned a thing or 2. 

Go to the link in my bio if you would like me to email you a free 4 part podcast series on how to start your first VRBO! 😘😘

We are headed to our home in Florida for a week for spring break!  Can’t wait!! 

You can see our home and the VRBO listing on the IG account @boujeeonthebeach 

Curious if you are a beach lover or a mountain girl??

I love love, love, love our half bath at @boujeeinthedesert. 

You can hear me in the video when we bought the house trying to convince myself that the bathroom was “OK the way it was”. Lol. I should have known better. 

Wallpaper is from @spoonflower. 

The cutest sign ever is from Etsy. 

I know so many people are afraid of putting dark colors in small rooms but I personally love it! 

How about you????

I love love LOVE the kids bunkroom at @boujeeinthedesert. 

But I made soooooo many mistakes in this room. 

1. the bunk beds are not super sturdy. I saw them online (see the last photo) and thought they were so cute but the truth is they have a maximum of 200 pounds. Since we use the house as an Airbnb, we’ve had to note that on the bed itself to make sure only kids are on it.

2. We left carpet in the bedroom and in retrospect I wish that we would have switched it to tile. Now to replace the carpet is going to require taking down the entire bed …. which we hired someone to come put up for us originally anyway. It was a huge assembly mess. (See pic)

3. After the beds were assembled is when I decided the room needed a rug. 🙈 I know some people don’t like rugs on top of carpet, but I personally do. But it took about 5 grown men to lift the beds up while several of us tried to scoot a rug underneath. I did it totally backwards. 😩😩

4. Originally I just wanted this wallpaper from @wall.blush on the TV wall. After it was done I decided that I wanted it on the wall around the window as well. So @yourgalfridayaz had to try to line up the pattern in the corner. She did a phenomenal job. But ugggggh. I made it hard. 

5. The light is beautiful and really does secure the fan blades so that no little fingers can touch it. But the cage around it prevents any air flow from the fan. There is no air movement out of that fan. None. Zilch. Lol. So cute…. But useless. 

Hopefully this makes someone feel better about your own decorating decisions today. If you feel like you’re constantly get stuff wrong …welcome to the club. Lol. And yet…. this is how we learn.

If you’re looking to buy your first Airbnb or VRBO, I do have a free 4 part podcast series in my link in bio that you can click on and hopefully it will help you to alleviate some costly boo-boos. 

My gift to you!! 😘😘

(I included a few before pictures of this room from when we bought the house as well! It used to be a craft room!)
